The Rivers State Police Command has paraded three women, Favour Ajuzie, Chioma Chibuike and Comfort Abatuo, who allegedly stole two babies identified as Favour Boniface and Miracle Boniface over two years ago. The command also paraded one Adamu Siraju, who is involved in using military uniform and G3 Rifle to rob his victims and one Osagie Igienhon also known as General who allegedly Kidnapped one Ekuchie Ogbonna sometime in December, 2021 at Oyigbo area. Commissioner of Police, Friday Eboka who paraded the suspects said “policemen on patrol around at oil mill market by Eleme Junction intercepted a tricycle and recovered a locally made pistol from Usman Suleiman and Iliyasu Musa” who are both 18 years old. CP also disclosed that “Austin Asomeji, Chairman of the All Progressives Congress in Emohua Local Government Area who was kidnapped on the 8th of February, 2022 along NTA road, Apara link road has been rescued and his saloon car recovered” while the suspects Barisitam Nbianee and Miracle Victor have been arrested. The Commissioner of Police used the opportunity to advise parents “to be vigilant while taking their children to market places as criminals have devised new tactics of abducting children”. The police commissioner also assured that those arrested will be charged to court at the end of investigation.